## PHASE 4 — Map Building

> Goal: All 4 zones exist and are playable end-to-end.

### Step 4.1 — Build Airlock Entry (Tutorial Zone)
🔨 This is the first area. No enemies here — just atmosphere and learning.

Layout (build with Parts/Unions in Studio):
```
[Spawn Point]
     ↓
[Dark airlock corridor — 20 studs long, 6 wide, 8 tall]
     ↓
[Crashed hallway — debris blocking path, player must jump over]
     ↓
[Checkpoint 1 — invisible Part triggers save]
     ↓
[Door to Engineering Deck — locked until Checkpoint 1 reached]
```

Lighting notes:
- Ambient = 0 (pitch black)
- Each wall sconce has a `PointLight`, Brightness=2, Range=15, Color=red
- Add 2–3 flickering lights (tag them `FlickerLight` for the atmosphere system)
- Add a crashed body prop (dummy model) with a Sound for atmosphere

### Step 4.2 — Build Engineering Deck (Zone 1)
🔨 First combat zone. 3–4 interconnected rooms.

Layout:
```
[Entry corridor from Airlock]
     ↓
[Engine Room A — 2 Necromorphs patrolling]
     ↓
[Tight maintenance tunnel — forces slow movement]
     ↓
[Ammo crate room — reward for exploring]
     ↓
[Engine Room B — 3 Necromorphs, one spawns from ceiling vent]
     ↓
[Checkpoint 2]
     ↓
[Stairwell to Medical Bay]
```

Enemy placement:
- Engine Room A: 2 Standard Necromorphs with 3 patrol waypoints each
- Engine Room B: 2 Standard + 1 Crawler (hiding under machinery)

### Step 4.3 — Build Medical Bay (Zone 2)
🔨 Wider, more open. Crawlers are the main threat here.

Layout:
```
[Entry from Engineering stairwell]
     ↓
[Reception area — 4 hospital beds, 2 Crawlers under them (jump scare)]
     ↓
[Surgery room — health kit pickup, flickering operating lights]
     ↓
[Morgue corridor — 5 body bags, one is a Necromorph (scripted reveal)]
     ↓
[Checkpoint 3]
     ↓
[Elevator shaft to Reactor Core]
```

Scripted moment (jumpscare):
- Body bag 3 is a Necromorph model set invisible
- When player walks within 10 studs: loud sting sound + model becomes visible + AI activates

### Step 4.4 — Build Reactor Core (Zone 3 / Final Area)
🔨 Large open room. This is the boss arena.

Layout:
```
[Elevator arrives]
     ↓
[Reactor floor — circular room, 60 studs diameter]
     ↓
[Reactor console in center — interact to "activate escape"]
     ↓
[Boss wave: 3 Standard + 2 Crawlers spawn from vents when console activated]
     ↓
[Survive 60 seconds]
     ↓
[Escape pod door opens — players reach it → Victory]
```

### Step 4.5 — Add Flickering Lights System
🤖 Claude creates `StarterPlayer/StarterPlayerScripts/AtmosphereController` (LocalScript):

- Finds all Parts tagged `FlickerLight` in the workspace
- For each one: runs a TweenService loop that randomly varies `PointLight.Brightness` between 0.2 and 2.5 with randomized intervals (0.05s–0.3s)
- Effect: each light flickers independently, creating organic horror atmosphere

### Step 4.6 — Add Personal Flashlight
🤖 Claude adds to `AtmosphereController`:
- Creates a `SpotLight` attached to the player's Head
- Brightness=5, Range=40, Angle=30 (narrow beam, like Dead Space)
- Players can toggle it with `F` key (off during scripted sequences for horror effect)

### Step 4.7 — Add Spatial Enemy Audio
🔨 For each Necromorph model in the Map:
1. Insert a `Sound` inside the Necromorph's Torso Part
2. Set SoundId to a groan/growl audio asset
3. Set `RollOffMaxDistance = 50` (fades with distance)
4. Set `Looped = true`

🤖 Claude adds code to `NecromorphAI` to start/stop the Sound based on enemy state.

### Step 4.8 — Playtest Phase 4 (Full Run)
🔨 Test with 2–4 players via Local Server:
- [ ] Full run from Airlock → Reactor takes ~20 minutes
- [ ] Flickering lights work in all zones
- [ ] Spatial audio works (enemy groans get louder as you approach)
- [ ] Boss wave spawns when console is activated
- [ ] Escape pod triggers Victory screen

